h1. BAMOE 8.0 to 9.4 Migration - Scheduler Component Analysis

h2. 1. Overview

This document covers the technical analysis and migration approach for the Scheduler component as part of the BAMOE 8.0 to 9.4 migration of the *status-mgmt-api* Spring Boot application.

The scheduler component is responsible for triggering robotic queue processing at configured times. It allows operations teams to view, reschedule, and cancel queue schedules via the Home Screen UI.

----

h2. 2. Old Architecture (BAMOE 8.x)

h3. 2.1 Component Stack

|| Component || Class/Interface || Role ||
| UI Screen | HomeScreenController | Exposes schedule/cancel endpoints |
| Service Layer | SchedulerInfoServiceImpl | Orchestrates schedule/cancel/list logic |
| Execution Bridge | OlaResponseQServiceImpl (x14) | Command + Reoccurring implementations |
| Scheduler Engine | org.kie.api.executor.ExecutorService | jBPM built-in async executor |
| Persistence | REQUESTINFO table | Stored all scheduled job state in Oracle |
| Queue Execution | QSchedulerServiceImpl | Did actual task processing via jBPM APIs |

h3. 2.2 Old Flow

{code:title=Old Scheduler Flow}
Application Startup
  → Each *ServiceImpl.getScheduleTime() [Reoccurring]
  → ExecutorService.scheduleRequest(commandName, date, CommandContext)
  → Persisted to REQUESTINFO table in Oracle

UI: getRoboticQList()
  → ExecutorService.getQueuedRequests()
  → Reads REQUESTINFO table → returns {queueName: nextFireTime}

UI: updateRoboticQTimer(ON, queueName, newDateTime)
  → ExecutorService.cancelRequest(existingId)
  → ExecutorService.scheduleRequest(commandName, newDate, ctx)

UI: updateRoboticQTimer(OFF, queueName)
  → ExecutorService.cancelRequest(requestId)

At Scheduled Time:
  → ExecutorService fires Command
  → OlaResponseQServiceImpl.execute(CommandContext)
  → QSchedulerService.trigger(queueName)
  → Processes user tasks via jBPM RuntimeDataService/UserTaskService
{code}

h3. 2.3 Old Properties Configuration

{code:title=Old application.properties - Scheduler Runtimes}
roboticqueue.olaresponseq.runtime=0 0 * * * ?
roboticqueue.nointerfaceq.runtime=0 10 * * * ?
roboticqueue.ntcholdq.runtime=0 0 0/4 * * ?
roboticqueue.ngcback.runtime=0 0 0/2 * * ?
roboticqueue.logCleanup.runtime=0 0 23 * * ?
roboticqueue.caslssq.runtime=0 30 0/4 * * ?
roboticqueue.nodeq.runtime=0 30 0/2 * * ?
roboticqueue.nouploadq.runtime=0 30 0/4 * * ?
roboticqueue.batchResubmitq.runtime=0 40 0/4 * * ?
roboticqueue.lapsedProcess.runtime=0 0 8 * * ?
retriggerOnlineapp.runtime=#{300 * 1000}
{code}

h3. 2.4 Old APIs Used (All Removed in BAMOE 9.x)

|| Old Class/Interface || Package || Purpose ||
| ExecutorService | org.kie.api.executor | Schedule/cancel/query jobs |
| ExecutionResults | org.kie.api.executor | Return type from Command.execute() |
| CommandContext | org.kie.api.executor | Input context to Command |
| Command | org.kie.api.executor | Interface for executable jobs |
| Reoccurring | org.kie.api.executor | Interface for recurring job schedule time |
| RequestInfo | org.kie.api.executor | Represents a scheduled job record |
| STATUS | org.kie.api.executor | QUEUED / RUNNING / CANCELLED enum |
| RuntimeDataService | org.jbpm.services.api | Query user tasks |
| AdvanceRuntimeDataService | org.jbpm.services.api | Advanced task query with variables |
| UserTaskService | org.jbpm.services.api | Claim/start/complete tasks |
| UserTaskInstanceWithPotOwnerDesc | org.jbpm.services.api.model | Task data object |
| QueryParam / QueryContext | org.kie.internal.query | Query filters and pagination |

*All of the above packages are completely removed in BAMOE 9.x / Kogito.*

----

h2. 3. Migration Options Considered

h3. 3.1 Option A - Kogito Jobs Service (REJECTED)

h4. What It Is

The Kogito Jobs Service is a built-in scheduling component available in BAMOE 9.x via the following dependencies:

{code:lang=groovy|title=Jobs Service Dependencies}
implementation 'org.kie:kogito-addons-springboot-embedded-jobs'
implementation 'org.kie:kogito-addons-springboot-embedded-jobs-jpa'
implementation 'org.kie.kogito:kogito-addons-springboot-jobs-management'
{code}

It is already present in the migrated project's build.gradle and application.properties.

h4. POC Findings

A proof of concept was conducted to determine whether Jobs Service could replace the old ExecutorService for scheduler queue management.

{code:lang=java|title=Jobs Service POC Attempt}
// Attempted: Schedule a non-BPMN job via Jobs Service
ProcessJobDescription job = ProcessJobDescription.of(
    ExactExpirationTime.of(ZonedDateTime.now().plusMinutes(2)),
    "TEST_PROCESS"
);
String jobId = jobsService.scheduleJob(job);
{code}

*POC Result:* The Jobs Service requires a valid BPMN process definition to exist for the scheduled callback. It fires an HTTP callback to a BPMN process endpoint. It cannot instantiate an arbitrary Java class by name and call an execute() method.

h4. Why Jobs Service Was Rejected

|| Reason || Detail ||
| BPMN-only design | Jobs Service is designed exclusively to advance BPMN process instance timers. It fires HTTP callbacks to BPMN runtime endpoints only. |
| No Command pattern support | The old system used Command interface implementations (OlaResponseQServiceImpl etc.) identified by class name. Jobs Service has no equivalent concept. |
| No arbitrary Java execution | Jobs Service cannot call QSchedulerService.trigger(queueName) directly. It can only POST to a BPMN process endpoint. |
| No schedule/cancel/list API equivalent | Jobs Service has no equivalent to ExecutorService.getQueuedRequests(), getRequestsByCommand(), or cancelRequest() that works outside BPMN context. |
| IBM documentation confirms gap | IBM BAMOE 9.4 migration tutorials (13 tutorials) contain no migration path for ExecutorService used outside BPMN process context. Tutorial 12 (Database Integration and Async Processing) covers Jobs Service only for BPMN timer callbacks. |
| No UI state mapping | Jobs Service has no concept of QUEUED/RUNNING/CANCELLED states equivalent to the old RequestInfo.getStatus() used to populate the UI scheduler table. |

h4. IBM Documentation Reference

From the official BAMOE 9.4 migration tutorials page:
[https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/ibamoe/9.4.x?topic=80x-using-bamoe-migration-tutorials]

*Tutorial 12 - Database Integration and Async Processing* covers Jobs Service only for integrating BPMN process timer callbacks. No tutorial covers migration of ExecutorService used for non-BPMN arbitrary Java command execution.

From the Apache KIE Kogito Jobs Service wiki:
"The Jobs Service receives requests of job scheduling and it sends a request at the time specified on the job request... The REST endpoint that is provided with the add-on is responsible for receiving the callbacks from Job Service at exact time when the timer was scheduled and by that move *the process instance execution forward*."

This confirms Jobs Service is BPMN process execution only.

----

h3. 3.2 Option B - Spring TaskScheduler / ScheduledFuture (REJECTED)

h4. What It Is

Spring Boot's built-in in-memory task scheduler using @Scheduled, TaskScheduler, and ScheduledFuture.

h4. Why It Was Rejected

|| Reason || Detail ||
| Not multi-pod safe | ScheduledFuture objects are stored in JVM memory per pod. On pod restart all scheduled tasks are lost even though the DB record remains. |
| OpenShift / APAAS risk | The application runs on OpenShift with multiple pods. An in-memory scheduler fires on every pod simultaneously causing duplicate queue processing. |
| No persistence | No equivalent to REQUESTINFO table. Scheduled state is lost on restart. |
| No cancel/reschedule equivalent | ScheduledFuture.cancel() only works within the same pod and same JVM lifetime. |
| UI state mismatch | Cannot reproduce QUEUED/RUNNING/CANCELLED states for the scheduler UI table. |
| Previous BPMN timer issue | The team already experienced the multi-pod timer duplication problem with BPMN timers. Spring in-memory scheduler has the same problem. |

----

h3. 3.3 Option C - Quartz Scheduler with JDBCJobStore (SELECTED)

h4. What It Is

Quartz is a Java job scheduling library that supports clustered, database-backed job scheduling. Spring Boot provides first-class integration via spring-boot-starter-quartz.

h4. Why Quartz Was Selected

|| Reason || Detail ||
| DB-backed persistence | All job state stored in QRTZ_* Oracle tables. Survives pod restarts. Exact structural equivalent of old REQUESTINFO table. |
| Multi-pod / cluster safe | JDBCJobStore with isClustered=true uses pessimistic DB locking. Only one pod fires a given job even across N pods. Solves the multi-pod problem completely. |
| QRTZ_* tables already exist | All 11 Quartz tables (QRTZ_JOB_DETAILS, QRTZ_TRIGGERS, QRTZ_CRON_TRIGGERS etc.) are already present in the RPAM Oracle schema and are empty. No DDL required. |
| Full cron support | Quartz CronTrigger directly replaces the old Reoccurring.getScheduleTime() cron expressions. Same cron format (Quartz cron). |
| One-time override support | Quartz SimpleTrigger supports one-time fire at a specific date/time. Directly replaces ExecutorService.scheduleRequest(commandName, date, ctx). |
| Cancel / pause support | Quartz Scheduler.unscheduleJob() and pauseTrigger() directly replace ExecutorService.cancelRequest(). |
| List queued jobs | Quartz Scheduler.getJobKeys() + getTrigger() replace ExecutorService.getQueuedRequests(). |
| No BPMN dependency | Quartz executes arbitrary Java logic via the Job interface. Directly supports calling QSchedulerService.trigger(queueName). |
| DisallowConcurrentExecution | @DisallowConcurrentExecution annotation prevents duplicate execution of the same job across pods at the cluster level. |
| Spring Boot auto-configuration | spring-boot-starter-quartz integrates with Spring context. @Autowired works inside Job classes via SpringBeanJobFactory. |
| Minimal code change | Controller, QSchedulerService interface, QSchedulerServiceImpl business logic, and UI are all unchanged. |

----

h2. 4. Migration Mapping - Old vs New

h3. 4.1 API Mapping

|| Old (BAMOE 8.x) || New (BAMOE 9.x / Quartz) ||
| org.kie.api.executor.ExecutorService | org.quartz.Scheduler (via ExecutorServiceAdapter) |
| ExecutorService.scheduleRequest(name, date, ctx) | ExecutorServiceAdapter.scheduleRequest() → Quartz SimpleTrigger |
| ExecutorService.cancelRequest(id) | ExecutorServiceAdapter.cancelRequest() → Scheduler.unscheduleJob() |
| ExecutorService.getQueuedRequests(QueryContext) | ExecutorServiceAdapter.getQueuedRequests() → Scheduler.getJobKeys() |
| ExecutorService.getRequestsByCommand(name, STATUS.QUEUED) | ExecutorServiceAdapter.isQueued(commandName) |
| ExecutorService.getRequestsByCommand(name, STATUS.RUNNING) | ExecutorServiceAdapter.isRunning(commandName) |
| Command.execute(CommandContext) | CommandExecutorJob.execute(JobExecutionContext) |
| Reoccurring.getScheduleTime() | SchedulerStartupSeeder → seedCronJob() → Quartz CronTrigger |
| RequestInfo.getTime() | Trigger.getNextFireTime() |
| RequestInfo.getStatus() QUEUED | TriggerState.NORMAL / WAITING |
| RequestInfo.getStatus() RUNNING | Scheduler.getCurrentlyExecutingJobs() |
| RequestInfo.getStatus() CANCELLED | Trigger paused or absent |
| REQUESTINFO Oracle table | QRTZ_JOB_DETAILS + QRTZ_TRIGGERS + QRTZ_CRON_TRIGGERS |
| org.kie.api.executor.ExecutionResults | com.barclays.api.status.mgmt.schedular.model.ExecutionResults (custom) |

h3. 4.2 Class Mapping

|| Old Class || New Class || Change Type ||
| OlaResponseQServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Replaced (all 14 Command impls → single Job class) |
| NoInterfaceQServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| NTCHoldQServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| NGCBckServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| LogCleanUpServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| CASLSSQServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| NODEQServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| NoUploadQServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| BatchResubmitQServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| LapsedProcessServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| FailedSoftToHardServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| ApplicationExpiryProcessServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| AdvancedLogCleanUpServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| SMSRetryServiceImpl | CommandExecutorJob | Deleted |
| SchedulerInfoServiceImpl | SchedulerInfoServiceImpl | Modified (~5 call sites only) |
| QSchedulerServiceImpl (jBPM APIs) | QSchedulerServiceImpl (GraphQL + REST) | Rewritten |
| N/A | ExecutorServiceAdapter | New - adapter layer |
| N/A | SchedulerStartupSeeder | New - replaces Reoccurring |
| N/A | SchedulerUtils | New - holds cron properties |
| N/A | QuartzConfig | New - datasource wiring |
| N/A | ExecutionResults (custom) | New - replaces org.kie.api.executor.ExecutionResults |
| HomeScreenController | HomeScreenController | Unchanged |
| SchedulerConstants | SchedulerConstants | Minor additions only |

h3. 4.3 QSchedulerServiceImpl Internal API Mapping

|| Old jBPM 8 API || New BAMOE 9.x API ||
| RuntimeDataService.getTasksAssignedAsPotentialOwnerByStatus() | GraphQL UserTaskInstances query via graphQlRestClient |
| AdvanceRuntimeDataService.queryUserTasksByVariables() | GraphQL UserTaskInstances with name + state filter |
| UserTaskInstanceWithPotOwnerDesc | UserTaskInstance (com.barclays.api.status.mgmt.model.graphql) |
| UserTaskService.claim(taskId, userId) | REST POST /usertasks/instance/{id}/transition {transitionId: claim} |
| UserTaskService.start(taskId, userId) | REST POST /usertasks/instance/{id}/transition {transitionId: start} |
| UserTaskService.complete(taskId, userId, vars) | REST POST /usertasks/instance/{id}/transition {transitionId: complete} |
| ProcessService.setProcessVariable() | ProcessUtilService.setProcessVariable() (already migrated) |
| task.getCorrelationKey() → caseId | processInstance.businessKey via nested GraphQL query |
| task.getCreatedOn() | UserTaskInstance.started (Instant) |
| task.getActualOwner() | UserTaskInstance.actualOwner |
| PeopleAssignments.getPotentialOwners() | UserTaskInstance.potentialUsers (List<String>) |
| kjars.getMainContainer() filter | Removed - no KJar/deployment concept in BAMOE 9.x |

