h2. 5. New Architecture (BAMOE 9.x)

h3. 5.1 Component Stack

|| Component || Class || Role ||
| UI Screen | HomeScreenController | Unchanged |
| Service Layer | SchedulerInfoServiceImpl | Modified - uses ExecutorServiceAdapter |
| Adapter Layer | ExecutorServiceAdapter | New - wraps Quartz, mimics old ExecutorService API |
| Startup Seeding | SchedulerStartupSeeder | New - seeds cron jobs on startup |
| Job Execution | CommandExecutorJob | New - Quartz Job, calls QSchedulerService.trigger() |
| Queue Execution | QSchedulerServiceImpl | Rewritten - uses GraphQL + REST |
| Scheduler Engine | org.quartz.Scheduler | Quartz JDBCJobStore |
| Persistence | QRTZ_* Oracle tables (11 tables) | Already present in RPAM schema |
| Task Query | GraphQL via graphQlRestClient | Queries RPAM.TASKS (Data Index) |
| Task Execution | REST via localRestClient | BAMOE 9.x user task transition API |

h3. 5.2 New Flow

{code:title=New Scheduler Flow}
Application Startup
  → SchedulerStartupSeeder.onApplicationEvent()
  → ExecutorServiceAdapter.seedCronJob(commandName, cronExpression)
  → Quartz CronTrigger persisted to QRTZ_CRON_TRIGGERS + QRTZ_JOB_DETAILS
  → (safe to call repeatedly - skips if job already exists)

UI: getRoboticQList()
  → SchedulerInfoServiceImpl.getRoboticQList()
  → ExecutorServiceAdapter.getQueuedRequests()
  → Quartz Scheduler.getJobKeys() + getTrigger()
  → Returns {queueDisplayName: nextFireTime} - same format as old UI

UI: updateRoboticQTimer(ON, queueName, newDateTime)
  → SchedulerInfoServiceImpl.updateDate()
  → ExecutorServiceAdapter.cancelRequest() [removes existing one-time trigger]
  → ExecutorServiceAdapter.scheduleRequest(commandName, newDate, ctx)
  → Quartz SimpleTrigger persisted to QRTZ_SIMPLE_TRIGGERS

UI: updateRoboticQTimer(OFF, queueName)
  → SchedulerInfoServiceImpl.updateDate()
  → ExecutorServiceAdapter.cancelRequest()
  → Quartz trigger unscheduled / paused

At Scheduled Time (Quartz fires - one pod only due to cluster locking):
  → CommandExecutorJob.execute(JobExecutionContext)
  → toQueueName(commandName) [maps class name to queue name constant]
  → QSchedulerService.trigger(queueName)
  → fetchTasksByName() via GraphQL → RPAM.TASKS
  → For each task: executeTask()
    → REST claim/start → localRestClient
    → ProcessUtilService.setProcessVariable()
    → updateUserInCaseLockTable() → VECTUSCASE.VEC_CASELOCK
    → REST complete → localRestClient
{code}

h3. 5.3 Database Tables Used

|| Table || Schema || Purpose || Status ||
| QRTZ_JOB_DETAILS | RPAM | Stores job definitions | Already exists, empty |
| QRTZ_TRIGGERS | RPAM | Stores trigger state | Already exists, empty |
| QRTZ_CRON_TRIGGERS | RPAM | Stores cron expressions | Already exists, empty |
| QRTZ_SIMPLE_TRIGGERS | RPAM | Stores one-time overrides | Already exists, empty |
| QRTZ_FIRED_TRIGGERS | RPAM | Tracks firing state for cluster | Already exists, empty |
| QRTZ_LOCKS | RPAM | Cluster pessimistic locking | Already exists, empty |
| QRTZ_SCHEDULER_STATE | RPAM | Pod heartbeat tracking | Already exists, empty |
| RPAM.TASKS | RPAM | Data Index - user task query source | Active |
| VECTUSCASE.VEC_CASELOCK | VECTUSCASE | Case lock update during task execution | Active |

