h2. 10. Risks and Mitigations

|| Risk || Severity || Mitigation ||
| Quartz tables not present in environment | High | Verified - all 11 QRTZ_* tables present in RPAM schema, empty, ready to use |
| getCaseId() incorrect before scheduler tasks in RPAM.TASKS | Medium | 3-level fallback implemented: processInstance.businessKey → externalReferenceId → PROCESS_INSTANCE_STATE_LOG.BUSINESS_KEY |
| localRestClient base URL incorrect for task transitions | Medium | Verify kogito.service.url in properties matches application endpoint |
| Quartz datasource conflict with BAMOE datasource | Low | QuartzConfig explicitly wires to bamoeDataSource via @QuartzDataSource |
| Command class names in QRTZ_JOB_DETAILS reference deleted classes | Low | CommandExecutorJob uses commandName as data key only, classes not instantiated |
| Scheduler not fired on first pod startup if tables empty | Low | SchedulerStartupSeeder runs on ApplicationReadyEvent and seeds all 10 queues |
| RetriggerOnlineAppsSchedular affected | None | RetriggerOnlineAppsSchedular uses @Scheduled(fixedRateString) - completely separate, unchanged |

----

h2. 11. Verification Steps

h3. After Deployment

{code:lang=sql|title=Verify Quartz Jobs Seeded}
-- Should return 10 rows after first startup
SELECT JOB_NAME, JOB_GROUP, DESCRIPTION
FROM RPAM.QRTZ_JOB_DETAILS
WHERE SCHED_NAME = 'CASScheduler';

-- Should return 10 cron triggers
SELECT JOB_NAME, TRIGGER_NAME, CRON_EXPRESSION,
       TO_CHAR(NEXT_FIRE_TIME/1000, '99999999999') AS NEXT_FIRE_EPOCH
FROM RPAM.QRTZ_CRON_TRIGGERS
WHERE SCHED_NAME = 'CASScheduler';
{code}

{code:lang=sql|title=Verify UI getRoboticQList Response}
-- Call via browser or Postman:
-- GET /retrieveAppDetails/queueList/getRoboticQList
-- Expected: JSON array with 10 entries [{queueName: nextFireTime}]
{code}

{code:lang=sql|title=Verify Reschedule}
-- After UI submit ON with new time, check:
SELECT TRIGGER_NAME, NEXT_FIRE_TIME
FROM RPAM.QRTZ_SIMPLE_TRIGGERS
WHERE SCHED_NAME = 'CASScheduler';
{code}

{code:lang=sql|title=Verify Cancel}
-- After UI submit OFF, trigger should be absent or paused:
SELECT TRIGGER_NAME, TRIGGER_STATE
FROM RPAM.QRTZ_TRIGGERS
WHERE SCHED_NAME = 'CASScheduler';
{code}

----

h2. 12. Decision Summary

{panel:title=Final Decision: Quartz Scheduler with JDBCJobStore|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#36B37E|titleBGColor=#36B37E|titleColor=#FFFFFF}
*Approach:* Replace org.kie.api.executor.ExecutorService with Quartz Scheduler using JDBCJobStore backed by the existing RPAM Oracle schema QRTZ_* tables.

*Reason Jobs Service rejected:* BPMN-process-only design. Cannot execute arbitrary Java Command classes. No equivalent to getQueuedRequests() / cancelRequest() outside BPMN context. Confirmed by IBM documentation and POC.

*Reason Spring TaskScheduler rejected:* In-memory only. Not safe across multiple OpenShift pods. State lost on pod restart.

*Why Quartz:* DB-backed, cluster-safe, full cron + one-time scheduling, cancel/pause support, arbitrary Java execution, Spring Boot native integration, QRTZ tables already present in RPAM schema.

*UI impact:* Zero. Controller, response format, and user journey identical to old system.

*Code impact:* 14 Command classes deleted, 1 adapter class added, 5 call sites changed in SchedulerInfoServiceImpl, QSchedulerServiceImpl rewritten to use GraphQL + REST.
{panel}

----

